ages exchanged between friends, and the fetus dolls given to children in school-she argues that activists made fetal life feel personal to many Americans. Pro-life activists persuaded people to see themselves in the pins, images, and dolls they held in their hands and made the fight against abortion the primary bread-and-butter issue for social conservatives. Holland ultimately demonstrates that the success of the pro-life movement lies in the borrowed logic and emotional power of leftist activism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPro-life movementzWest (U.S.)vCase studies. 0aPro-life movementzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Abortion & Birth Control.2bisacsh  aabortion clinics.  aabortion.  aactivism.  aanti abortion movements.  aconservative movements.  aconservative politics.  afetal life.  afetal pins.  afetus dolls.  agraphic images.  agrassroots.  ahistory.  alegalized abortion.  apathos.  apolitical movements.  apolitics.  apro choice.  apro life.  areproductive rights.  arhetoric.  asocial change.  asocial conservatives.  asocial issues.  awomens health.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520968479zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968479423Coveruhttps://ww